tary","header":"Served Confederate ambulance corps; became America's best-known Mason","body":"Isaacs rendered service to the Confederacy through the Ambulance Corps during the Civil War, then turned that community of service into a Masonic career of national scope. He became Grand Secretary of the Masonic grand bodies of Virginia and Grand Recorder of the Grand Encampment of Knights Templar — described by contemporaries as personally known to more Masons than any other man in the country."},{"number":2,"category":"career","header":"Married Masonic Grand Secretary's daughter","body":"Isaacs married Julia Lee Dove, daughter of Dr. John Dove, Grand Secretary of the Masonic grand bodies of Virginia, and began assisting his father-in-law in the position. When Dr. Dove died in 1876, Isaacs was chosen to succeed him and held the office continuously until his own death in 1895."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"william-isaacs-1818"},"HD2790":{"id":"HD2790","has_descendants_documented":false,"is_placeholder":false,"gender":"male","classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"generation_from_thomas":8,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1788,"month":11,"day":5},"death":{},"parents":{"father_id":"X01910","mother_id":"H01239"},"marriages":[],"tags":[],"sources":[{"short":"St. John Genealogy"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"William Isaacs","first_name":"William","last_name":"Isaacs","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"william-isaacs-1788"},"HD2791":{"id":"HD2791","has_descendants_documented":false,"is_placeholder":false,"gender":"male","classification":{"incl